Global Chip Test Equipment Market Insights
Chip Test Equipment Market size was valued at USD 3.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 5.1 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Chip Test Equipment Market Overview
The global chip test equipment market was valued at approximately USD 7.5 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 5.8% from 2024 to 2032. The market is driven by increasing demand for advanced semiconductors in automotive, consumer electronics, and telecommunications industries. The rising complexity of integrated circuits (ICs) and the need for precision in testing, quality assurance, and reliability testing of chips are also key contributors. Regionally, North America and Asia-Pacific lead the market due to significant semiconductor manufacturing and technological advancements.

